WEBVTT

00:00:05.023 --> 00:00:07.663
I’m about to become a star.

00:00:07.703 --> 00:00:12.623
You don’t understand
what it’s like to grow up alone.

00:00:12.623 --> 00:00:13.943
Do you really want to be a star?

00:00:13.983 --> 00:00:18.463
Good acting isn’t just memorizing lines
or copying how someone else plays it.

00:00:18.503 --> 00:00:20.503
You have to act from inside…

00:00:21.143 --> 00:00:22.263
Let go.

00:00:22.463 --> 00:00:23.783
- Wanneung.
- Let go.

00:00:23.823 --> 00:00:25.223
- Wanneung.
- Let go.

00:00:28.943 --> 00:00:30.183
Are you hurt?

00:03:44.783 --> 00:03:45.903
You...

00:03:46.063 --> 00:03:47.183
You’re awake?

00:03:57.863 --> 00:03:59.103
How are you feeling?

00:04:03.023 --> 00:04:05.903
Still a little dizzy, you know.

00:04:09.863 --> 00:04:11.863
Thank you, Win.

00:04:11.863 --> 00:04:13.503
For helping me.

00:04:14.423 --> 00:04:16.183
If it wasn’t for you,

00:04:16.183 --> 00:04:18.303
I probably wouldn’t have made it.

00:04:21.303 --> 00:04:24.383
Next time, be more careful, okay?

00:04:24.503 --> 00:04:27.783
If someone asks you to cast
somewhere weird and secluded,

00:04:28.063 --> 00:04:29.263
and you don’t even know them,

00:04:29.263 --> 00:04:30.503
that’s dangerous.

00:04:31.383 --> 00:04:33.183
Just tell me next time.

00:04:33.223 --> 00:04:34.783
I can go with you.

00:04:37.063 --> 00:04:38.383
Okay, Win.

00:04:42.743 --> 00:04:43.783
You...

00:04:44.263 --> 00:04:45.423
Does it hurt?

00:04:47.423 --> 00:04:48.743
It hurts...

00:04:48.783 --> 00:04:50.063
back here.

00:04:50.463 --> 00:04:53.503
I think I must’ve hit it when...

00:04:53.583 --> 00:04:55.783
I fell and slammed into the floor.

00:04:57.063 --> 00:04:58.383
Let me see.

00:05:00.223 --> 00:05:01.223
You...

00:05:03.943 --> 00:05:05.583
I think it’s bruised.

00:05:06.223 --> 00:05:07.983
I’ll go get some ointment for you.

00:06:14.583 --> 00:06:15.583
You...

00:06:17.063 --> 00:06:18.983
Take your shirt off. I’ll apply it.

00:06:25.103 --> 00:06:26.823
We’re both girls. Why be shy?

00:06:31.383 --> 00:06:33.103
Then I’ll help you.

00:07:57.943 --> 00:07:58.943
I...

00:07:59.303 --> 00:08:00.503
I’m sorry.

00:08:18.103 --> 00:08:19.103
Does it hurt?

00:08:42.743 --> 00:08:44.423
Your back is bruised this badly.

00:08:44.663 --> 00:08:45.943
Shouldn’t we see a doctor?

00:08:45.943 --> 00:08:48.703
Just to check what’s going on inside.

00:08:50.263 --> 00:08:51.903
It’s not that serious.

00:08:52.423 --> 00:08:54.583
Once I put the ointment on, I’ll be fine.

00:08:55.463 --> 00:08:56.663
What you’re saying is,

00:08:56.663 --> 00:08:59.383
you haven’t even seen how big the bruise is.

00:08:59.543 --> 00:09:01.623
Let’s go see a doctor. Don’t be stubborn.

00:09:09.663 --> 00:09:10.823
Right there.

00:09:11.623 --> 00:09:13.183
We did another X-ray,

00:09:13.223 --> 00:09:14.263
and everything looks normal.

00:09:14.263 --> 00:09:16.423
It’s probably just a ligament strain.

00:09:16.463 --> 00:09:18.823
Then why does it still hurt so much?

00:09:19.823 --> 00:09:22.423
The doctor told you to rest your foot
for two to three days,

00:09:22.463 --> 00:09:23.983
and stop wearing high heels.

00:09:24.223 --> 00:09:25.383
If you’re not going to listen,

00:09:25.383 --> 00:09:26.903
why come see the doctor at all?

00:09:27.943 --> 00:09:30.303
I came here to get treated.

00:09:30.863 --> 00:09:33.423
Not to be told what to do all the time.

00:09:33.423 --> 00:09:35.743
I already said I have to wear heels.

00:09:35.783 --> 00:09:37.383
There are hundreds of crew members.

00:09:37.423 --> 00:09:40.183
You want me to skip work just
because my foot hurts?

00:09:40.223 --> 00:09:42.223
Everyone else would suffer for it.

00:09:42.263 --> 00:09:43.903
Fine. Do whatever you want.

00:09:44.543 --> 00:09:46.303
Wait until you can’t walk anymore,

00:09:46.463 --> 00:09:47.503
then stop.

00:09:48.343 --> 00:09:51.423
I’ll prescribe painkillers
and an ointment for you.

00:09:53.063 --> 00:09:54.103
All set.

00:10:13.943 --> 00:10:16.503
(Examination Room)

00:10:23.423 --> 00:10:24.703
Hello, Wanneung.

00:10:41.783 --> 00:10:44.343
I’ll go find parking
and come in to you right away.

00:10:44.703 --> 00:10:45.783
Okay, Win.

00:10:58.023 --> 00:11:00.223
Wanneung, how are you feeling?

00:11:02.223 --> 00:11:04.623
Who did you come with?

00:11:05.023 --> 00:11:06.223
Did you call a Grab?

00:11:08.183 --> 00:11:09.583
Yeah, a Grab.

00:11:09.583 --> 00:11:12.423
He saw that my back hurt,
so he let me sit in the front.

00:11:12.423 --> 00:11:13.823
So I’d be more comfortable.

00:11:14.263 --> 00:11:16.223
But this car feels kind of familiar.

00:11:16.263 --> 00:11:19.103
Like the one your mom’s friend
left at your house.

00:11:20.303 --> 00:11:22.623
Just happens to be the same model.

00:11:24.103 --> 00:11:25.783
- Let’s go, Meedee.
- Okay.

00:11:40.623 --> 00:11:41.703
Win.

00:11:49.623 --> 00:11:51.303
What are you doing here?

00:11:51.503 --> 00:11:52.743
Are you sick?

00:11:52.863 --> 00:11:54.023
No.

00:11:54.223 --> 00:11:56.583
I just had something to take care of.

00:11:57.983 --> 00:12:00.383
Your leg’s still not better?

00:12:02.903 --> 00:12:05.423
I’ve been working every day without rest.

00:12:06.423 --> 00:12:07.903
So my foot’s acting up again.

00:12:09.023 --> 00:12:10.463
So...

00:12:10.463 --> 00:12:12.103
what business did you have here?

00:12:13.823 --> 00:12:15.423
I came to visit a friend.

00:12:15.543 --> 00:12:16.703
I should get going.

00:12:26.903 --> 00:12:28.383
I’ll arrange the X-ray

00:12:28.383 --> 00:12:29.903
as the doctor ordered.

00:12:33.583 --> 00:12:35.263
You’re being so dramatic, Meedee.

00:12:35.263 --> 00:12:36.543
It’s just a small injury.

00:12:36.583 --> 00:12:38.023
Do I really need to be admitted?

00:12:38.063 --> 00:12:40.383
Even if it’s just a bruise,

00:12:40.423 --> 00:12:42.183
if the impact was strong,

00:12:42.183 --> 00:12:44.303
there could be internal bleeding.

00:12:44.343 --> 00:12:46.103
Or even a hairline fracture.

00:12:46.463 --> 00:12:48.423
You need an X-ray first.

00:12:48.743 --> 00:12:51.423
And you’re staying here overnight.

00:12:51.463 --> 00:12:52.823
Just to be safe.

00:12:53.143 --> 00:12:55.623
- But I’m fine.
- Wanneung.

00:12:58.183 --> 00:12:59.183
You know...

00:12:59.223 --> 00:13:01.103
how worried I am about you.

00:13:05.583 --> 00:13:06.743
Okay, okay.

00:13:06.743 --> 00:13:08.023
I’ll stay.

00:13:08.063 --> 00:13:09.103
Fine.

00:13:11.623 --> 00:13:14.103
But... I need to use the bathroom.

00:13:16.343 --> 00:13:17.903
I’ll take you.

00:13:18.263 --> 00:13:19.343
It’s okay.

00:13:19.383 --> 00:13:22.223
It’s just a bruise. I’m not disabled.

00:13:22.263 --> 00:13:23.503
I can go by myself.

00:13:59.823 --> 00:14:01.223
Hello, Wanneung.

00:14:01.623 --> 00:14:03.103
Hello, Win.

00:14:04.463 --> 00:14:05.703
So, the doctor...

00:14:06.183 --> 00:14:08.383
My friend says I have to be admitted.

00:14:08.543 --> 00:14:10.503
You can head home first.

00:14:11.343 --> 00:14:12.383
Well...

00:14:12.383 --> 00:14:15.103
My friend doesn’t know my mom sold the house.

00:14:15.143 --> 00:14:17.703
And she doesn’t know about you either.

00:14:18.103 --> 00:14:19.463
If she sees you...

00:14:19.463 --> 00:14:20.983
it’ll be obvious.

00:14:22.023 --> 00:14:23.183
Alright.

00:14:23.663 --> 00:14:25.423
Are you hungry?

00:14:25.503 --> 00:14:27.783
Want me to buy something
and leave it at the counter?

00:14:29.383 --> 00:14:30.823
No, it’s okay.

00:14:30.943 --> 00:14:32.223
Thank you.

00:14:34.223 --> 00:14:35.663
Okay, then...

00:14:35.703 --> 00:14:37.463
Get plenty of rest.

00:14:37.703 --> 00:14:38.943
I’ll pick you up tomorrow.

00:14:39.743 --> 00:14:42.823
Okay. Drive home safe.

00:16:39.343 --> 00:16:41.503
How are you going to make him know

00:16:42.023 --> 00:16:44.703
that you love him?

00:16:49.183 --> 00:16:50.423
Like this.

00:17:36.263 --> 00:17:37.623
I’m on my way to pick you up.

00:17:41.863 --> 00:17:42.903
You...

00:17:43.023 --> 00:17:44.303
You’re back?

00:17:45.663 --> 00:17:47.063
Well...

00:17:47.103 --> 00:17:48.583
My friend got an urgent case.

00:17:48.583 --> 00:17:50.823
So I slipped away and came back.

00:17:51.183 --> 00:17:53.423
But I didn’t tell her anything.

00:17:53.503 --> 00:17:56.023
Good thing I’m great at acting.

00:17:56.063 --> 00:17:57.823
The secret’s still safe.

00:17:59.543 --> 00:18:01.303
Great at acting?

00:18:02.463 --> 00:18:05.223
That’s because you have a good teacher.

00:18:06.223 --> 00:18:07.703
Well...

00:18:07.743 --> 00:18:09.423
Thank you, Teacher Win,

00:18:09.463 --> 00:18:11.263
for teaching me how to act.

00:18:15.583 --> 00:18:16.743
You...

00:18:16.823 --> 00:18:18.023
What’s wrong?

00:18:18.463 --> 00:18:19.663
I...

00:18:19.703 --> 00:18:20.903
My head’s a little itchy.

00:18:20.903 --> 00:18:23.423
I haven’t washed my hair yet.

00:18:23.463 --> 00:18:24.543
It’s like...

00:18:24.583 --> 00:18:27.423
there are a hundred ants crawling on my head.

00:18:29.023 --> 00:18:30.343
Does it still hurt?

00:18:30.583 --> 00:18:32.423
How are you supposed to wash it like this?

00:18:46.263 --> 00:18:47.623
Is that comfortable?

00:18:50.543 --> 00:18:51.983
Very comfortable.

00:18:53.223 --> 00:18:54.503
Thank you.

00:19:07.743 --> 00:19:08.903
You...

00:19:08.943 --> 00:19:09.943
Crazy.

00:19:10.383 --> 00:19:12.703
There’s so much, so much!

00:19:16.863 --> 00:19:18.303
You got it all over you.

00:19:40.503 --> 00:19:41.823
Wanneung.

00:19:53.583 --> 00:19:54.823
Wanneung.

00:20:34.183 --> 00:20:36.343
(Meedee)

00:20:54.583 --> 00:20:55.743
Hello, Wanneung.

00:20:59.263 --> 00:21:00.703
Wanneung’s sleeping.

00:21:00.943 --> 00:21:02.183
Who are you?

00:21:02.463 --> 00:21:04.503
And why are you answering
my girlfriend’s phone?

00:21:06.263 --> 00:21:07.303
Answer me.

00:21:30.263 --> 00:21:31.303
Wanneung.

00:21:31.343 --> 00:21:33.383
Wanneung, are you home?

00:21:33.423 --> 00:21:35.223
Come out and talk to me.

00:21:35.783 --> 00:21:37.503
I said she’s sleeping.

00:21:37.543 --> 00:21:38.823
Why are you yelling?

00:21:39.343 --> 00:21:40.503
And who are you?

00:21:41.063 --> 00:21:42.863
How are you in my girlfriend’s house?

00:21:42.903 --> 00:21:45.303
Why don’t you ask your friend
Wanneung yourself?

00:21:46.063 --> 00:21:47.583
That’s her personal matter.

00:21:47.903 --> 00:21:50.223
All you need to know is that she’s safe.

00:21:50.543 --> 00:21:52.063
If you don’t open the door,

00:21:52.063 --> 00:21:53.783
I’m calling the police.

00:21:53.823 --> 00:21:55.063
I should be the one calling.

00:21:55.103 --> 00:21:56.503
This is my house.

00:21:56.583 --> 00:21:58.703
You’re the one causing a scene.

00:21:59.023 --> 00:22:01.303
Standing in front of my house yelling like this.

00:22:01.823 --> 00:22:03.423
If you don’t want more trouble,

00:22:03.463 --> 00:22:04.623
go home.

00:22:05.463 --> 00:22:07.823
Take one step forward
and the cops are coming.

00:22:21.023 --> 00:22:22.543
Meedee just made that up.

00:22:22.583 --> 00:22:23.823
She’s not my girlfriend.

00:22:23.823 --> 00:22:25.743
Please don’t misunderstand, Win.

00:22:25.743 --> 00:22:27.503
I need to call and deal with her.

00:22:27.543 --> 00:22:29.943
She keeps saying that
and it ruins my reputation.

00:22:29.983 --> 00:22:32.423
Please don’t misunderstand, Win.

00:22:37.343 --> 00:22:40.023
Why are you so afraid I’d misunderstand?

00:22:41.503 --> 00:22:42.783
Well...

00:22:43.543 --> 00:22:44.823
I...

00:22:48.903 --> 00:22:51.223
Why are you smiling?

00:22:51.263 --> 00:22:52.943
Because you know I’m single?

00:23:06.143 --> 00:23:07.303
It’s getting cold.

00:23:07.343 --> 00:23:09.903
Aren’t you going to eat? You keep talking.

00:23:23.863 --> 00:23:25.223
Fine, I’ll eat.

00:23:32.943 --> 00:23:34.223
Does it still hurt?

00:23:34.823 --> 00:23:36.503
A little.

00:23:36.823 --> 00:23:37.903
It’s okay.

00:23:41.663 --> 00:23:43.103
Come here.

00:23:59.463 --> 00:24:00.463
Here.

00:24:05.703 --> 00:24:06.703
Is it good?

00:24:08.703 --> 00:24:09.823
How about this…

00:24:11.183 --> 00:24:12.783
When you’re fully recovered,

00:24:13.463 --> 00:24:15.623
I’ll teach you acting.

00:24:16.063 --> 00:24:17.303
Really?

00:24:17.583 --> 00:24:19.503
You’re not lying to me, right?

00:24:20.143 --> 00:24:21.903
Do I look like I’d lie?

00:24:23.263 --> 00:24:24.303
You’re seriously...

00:24:24.423 --> 00:24:27.503
like an angel sent from heaven.

00:24:29.543 --> 00:24:31.743
- Thank you.
- For what?

00:24:35.543 --> 00:24:37.503
Wanneung’s finally going to be a superstar,

00:24:37.503 --> 00:24:40.103
just like everyone else!

00:24:42.863 --> 00:24:43.863
You…

00:24:43.903 --> 00:24:45.583
sit down properly.

00:24:45.663 --> 00:24:47.663
I’m just excited!

00:24:47.663 --> 00:24:49.703
Then be excited sitting down.

00:24:51.063 --> 00:24:52.503
Thank you.

00:24:52.903 --> 00:24:54.543
You’re welcome.

00:24:56.783 --> 00:24:58.303
Can I have another bite?

00:24:59.463 --> 00:25:00.503
Sure.

00:25:18.543 --> 00:25:20.983
You promised to teach me acting.

00:25:20.983 --> 00:25:22.943
Do you still want to be a superstar?

00:25:22.943 --> 00:25:23.783
I do.

00:25:23.783 --> 00:25:25.023
Look into my eyes.

00:25:25.023 --> 00:25:27.543
And feel what I’m trying to tell you.

00:26:03.823 --> 00:26:04.823
Wanneung.

00:26:12.023 --> 00:26:13.463
What is it, Win?

00:26:14.223 --> 00:26:16.103
You’re going to work today, right?

00:26:18.143 --> 00:26:20.703
I just wanted to check if you’re really better.

00:26:21.503 --> 00:26:23.023
I’m all better.

00:26:23.063 --> 00:26:24.103
Want to see?

00:26:33.543 --> 00:26:34.703
Sorry.

00:26:37.423 --> 00:26:38.783
Does it still hurt?

00:26:41.223 --> 00:26:42.703
Not at all.

00:26:51.983 --> 00:26:53.543
I’ll...

00:26:53.543 --> 00:26:55.983
go get dressed or I’ll be late.

00:26:56.503 --> 00:26:57.703
Okay.

00:27:28.663 --> 00:27:29.903
All set.

00:27:31.343 --> 00:27:33.263
P’...

00:27:33.303 --> 00:27:34.983
Has Waanwaan not arrived yet?

00:27:35.343 --> 00:27:36.783
I don’t think so.

00:27:36.983 --> 00:27:39.823
I really need to see Waanwaan today.

00:27:39.823 --> 00:27:41.383
I volunteered for this event

00:27:41.423 --> 00:27:43.223
just because I wanted to see her.

00:27:43.263 --> 00:27:46.383
I know. But for now, go iron the clothes first.

00:27:46.543 --> 00:27:47.663
Okay.

00:27:56.023 --> 00:27:57.103
Ah you...

00:27:57.503 --> 00:27:58.583
What?

00:27:58.583 --> 00:28:01.383
Why didn’t you tell me May would be here today?

00:28:01.543 --> 00:28:03.183
You didn’t ask.

00:28:03.183 --> 00:28:04.303
You only asked

00:28:04.343 --> 00:28:06.503
if Waanwaan would be on set.

00:28:14.783 --> 00:28:15.783
Hey.

00:28:16.463 --> 00:28:18.103
Are you calling me?

00:28:18.143 --> 00:28:19.263
No.

00:28:20.423 --> 00:28:22.103
I’m talking to Wanneung.

00:28:29.903 --> 00:28:31.783
Hello, May.

00:28:33.503 --> 00:28:35.463
Help me carry stuff from the car.

00:28:39.023 --> 00:28:40.743
I need to iron the outfits.

00:28:40.783 --> 00:28:42.383
I’ll get someone else.

00:28:42.423 --> 00:28:43.903
Get who?

00:28:43.943 --> 00:28:45.343
Everyone’s busy.

00:28:45.383 --> 00:28:46.583
You go.

00:28:47.583 --> 00:28:48.583
Go.

00:28:49.423 --> 00:28:50.703
Go.

00:28:52.503 --> 00:28:54.423
Hurry up. Follow me.

00:29:12.863 --> 00:29:14.863
Can I have the car key?

00:29:16.823 --> 00:29:18.583
How do you know Win?

00:29:18.623 --> 00:29:20.983
Since when? Why didn’t I know?

00:29:23.223 --> 00:29:24.583
Well...

00:29:25.543 --> 00:29:27.583
I...

00:29:28.783 --> 00:29:31.183
I’m not anything with Win.

00:29:34.223 --> 00:29:36.183
If acting feels fake, it shows.

00:29:36.223 --> 00:29:38.183
Someone like you can’t lie smoothly.

00:29:38.543 --> 00:29:40.463
Or should I demonstrate for you?

00:29:40.503 --> 00:29:42.103
Which scene should we do?

00:29:42.823 --> 00:29:44.903
The lead gets shoved
by a jealous crew member,

00:29:44.943 --> 00:29:46.183
falls down,

00:29:46.543 --> 00:29:49.183
twists her ankle, can’t continue shooting,
and the set shuts down.

00:29:49.863 --> 00:29:52.063
How much would the damages be?

00:29:52.823 --> 00:29:54.703
Could you even afford it?

00:29:57.383 --> 00:29:58.903
I never thought

00:29:59.063 --> 00:30:01.303
a leading lady like you would be this vicious.

00:30:01.623 --> 00:30:03.463
Excuse me, I need to get back to work.

00:30:04.583 --> 00:30:06.183
- Wait.
- May.

00:30:09.303 --> 00:30:11.743
That scene really impressed me.

00:30:11.743 --> 00:30:13.103
I never thought

00:30:13.103 --> 00:30:15.423
a sweet-faced lead like you

00:30:15.463 --> 00:30:17.703
could play a villain so well.

00:30:17.903 --> 00:30:20.423
If you don’t want to be the lead,
why not say so?

00:30:20.463 --> 00:30:21.903
Should we let Gam

00:30:21.903 --> 00:30:23.983
step in as the lead instead?

00:30:24.023 --> 00:30:25.143
I could

00:30:25.183 --> 00:30:27.663
go inform the client myself.

00:30:34.023 --> 00:30:35.503
Hello, May.

00:30:39.503 --> 00:30:40.783
Hello, Waanwaan.

00:30:40.783 --> 00:30:42.143
My name is Wanneung.

00:30:42.183 --> 00:30:43.943
I really want to be an actress.

00:30:43.983 --> 00:30:46.183
Would you take me under your agency?

00:30:51.463 --> 00:30:53.863
Alright, let me get your number.

00:30:53.903 --> 00:30:55.903
If I find a good role that suits you,

00:30:56.543 --> 00:30:57.543
I’ll contact you.

00:30:57.863 --> 00:30:59.143
Really?

00:31:03.943 --> 00:31:05.143
Here’s my number.

00:31:05.183 --> 00:31:06.943
You can call me 24/7.

00:31:06.983 --> 00:31:08.303
I’ll be waiting.

00:31:08.983 --> 00:31:10.783
Just wait for my call.

00:31:11.943 --> 00:31:14.223
And don’t tell anyone
I asked for your number.

00:31:14.263 --> 00:31:16.063
It’s a business secret.

00:31:16.223 --> 00:31:19.063
Of course. I’ll keep my mouth shut.

00:31:19.103 --> 00:31:21.583
I’ll get back to work now.

00:31:31.423 --> 00:31:33.023
Gam, you heard that too, right?

00:31:33.023 --> 00:31:34.343
About Win and that girl.

00:31:34.623 --> 00:31:35.903
I did.

00:32:06.703 --> 00:32:08.783
What’s with you? Smiling to yourself.

00:32:09.983 --> 00:32:10.983
Nothing.

00:32:12.903 --> 00:32:14.903
Why are you so high-pitched?

00:32:15.423 --> 00:32:16.583
Nothing.

00:32:18.423 --> 00:32:20.783
Are you going to work out?

00:32:21.463 --> 00:32:22.583
Not me.

00:32:24.143 --> 00:32:25.143
Us.

00:32:26.463 --> 00:32:27.503
Us.

00:32:39.743 --> 00:32:41.463
I just got off work. I’m exhausted.

00:32:41.503 --> 00:32:43.023
And now you want me to run?

00:32:43.063 --> 00:32:44.383
You’re so mean.

00:32:44.383 --> 00:32:46.863
You promised to teach me acting.

00:32:46.903 --> 00:32:49.703
I’m not trying out for the national team.

00:32:49.983 --> 00:32:51.023
Exercise

00:32:51.063 --> 00:32:52.543
helps with focus.

00:32:52.583 --> 00:32:54.383
When your heart feels tired,

00:32:54.543 --> 00:32:56.103
your mind starts wandering.

00:32:56.663 --> 00:32:59.183
You won’t be fully committed
to what’s in front of you.

00:32:59.223 --> 00:33:00.303
You have to train.

00:33:02.423 --> 00:33:04.623
If you want me to work on focus,

00:33:04.623 --> 00:33:06.423
I could just meditate.

00:33:06.463 --> 00:33:09.103
No need to exhaust myself like this.

00:33:11.463 --> 00:33:13.103
Exercise

00:33:13.383 --> 00:33:15.023
keeps your body alert,

00:33:15.023 --> 00:33:17.503
makes your muscles more efficient.

00:33:17.703 --> 00:33:19.783
If you want to be an actor, you have to study.

00:33:20.103 --> 00:33:21.383
Understand that.

00:33:22.143 --> 00:33:24.303
Isn’t there anything easier?

00:33:24.343 --> 00:33:26.183
If you think being an actor

00:33:26.223 --> 00:33:29.343
is just dressing up,
walking around, getting famous and rich,

00:33:29.383 --> 00:33:30.823
you’re wrong.

00:33:31.743 --> 00:33:33.183
Being an actor

00:33:33.303 --> 00:33:35.183
is just as exhausting as any other job.

00:33:35.383 --> 00:33:36.903
Everything is about learning.

00:33:37.023 --> 00:33:38.623
Those famous K-pop singers…

00:33:38.663 --> 00:33:40.823
the ones who dance so powerfully…

00:33:40.823 --> 00:33:42.783
they train at least eight hours.

00:33:43.703 --> 00:33:45.223
Eight hours?

00:33:45.263 --> 00:33:47.703
If you want an easy job,

00:33:48.303 --> 00:33:49.863
acting isn’t it.

00:33:51.343 --> 00:33:54.223
Have I misunderstood this whole time?

00:33:54.703 --> 00:33:55.903
No wonder

00:33:55.943 --> 00:33:59.383
I’ve only been a background
extra walking past the camera.

00:34:02.623 --> 00:34:04.183
Eight hours...

00:34:06.303 --> 00:34:08.583
Do you still want to be a superstar?

00:34:09.743 --> 00:34:10.783
I do.

00:34:16.543 --> 00:34:17.543
Let’s go.

00:34:25.463 --> 00:34:28.263
- What’s next?
- Is it napping?

00:34:33.983 --> 00:34:35.183
Next,

00:34:35.303 --> 00:34:38.103
I’ll teach you to speak with your eyes.

00:34:38.263 --> 00:34:40.503
My eyes are already closing, Win.

00:34:40.543 --> 00:34:41.943
I’m sleepy.

00:34:41.983 --> 00:34:43.303
Wake up.

00:34:43.463 --> 00:34:44.983
This is a test.

00:34:46.223 --> 00:34:47.903
What do you want?

00:34:48.103 --> 00:34:50.823
Tell me with your eyes. Make me understand.

00:34:50.863 --> 00:34:51.903
But...

00:34:51.943 --> 00:34:53.983
How are we supposed to communicate like that?

00:34:54.023 --> 00:34:55.223
If you can’t do it,

00:34:55.263 --> 00:34:56.623
then you fail.

00:34:56.623 --> 00:34:58.063
And I won’t teach you anymore.

00:34:58.063 --> 00:34:59.423
Why are you so harsh?

00:34:59.463 --> 00:35:00.503
Start.

00:35:00.503 --> 00:35:02.343
I’m not even ready yet.

00:35:02.383 --> 00:35:03.383
Don’t talk.

00:35:03.703 --> 00:35:05.023
Show me.

00:35:05.263 --> 00:35:07.263
I’ll tell you if I understand.

00:35:10.983 --> 00:35:12.223
I...

00:35:12.263 --> 00:35:13.383
I can’t think of anything.

00:35:13.383 --> 00:35:15.383
I don’t know what to say to you.

00:35:23.463 --> 00:35:24.503
Alright.

00:35:25.663 --> 00:35:27.383
Look into my eyes.

00:35:27.383 --> 00:35:29.903
And feel what I’m trying to tell you.

00:35:41.743 --> 00:35:43.583
I want to tell you that...

00:35:44.143 --> 00:35:45.983
I have feelings for you.

00:35:55.543 --> 00:35:58.023
But the pain from my past makes me afraid.

00:35:58.743 --> 00:36:00.383
Can you wait for me, Wanneung?

00:36:01.303 --> 00:36:02.903
Don’t fall for anyone yet.

00:36:02.983 --> 00:36:04.863
Don’t open your heart to anyone.

00:36:04.983 --> 00:36:06.463
And when I’m ready,

00:36:06.703 --> 00:36:08.783
I’ll tell you how I feel myself.

00:36:09.663 --> 00:36:12.263
What are you really trying to tell me, Win?

00:36:12.863 --> 00:36:14.063
Why...

00:36:14.103 --> 00:36:16.383
Why do I feel this way?

00:36:17.303 --> 00:36:20.183
I shouldn’t have let
myself get this close to you.

00:36:20.663 --> 00:36:22.423
But I can’t help it.

00:36:22.463 --> 00:36:24.983
I want to be near you all the time.

00:36:25.783 --> 00:36:27.143
I know that...

00:36:27.183 --> 00:36:28.543
someone as perfect as you

00:36:28.543 --> 00:36:31.063
would never fall for someone silly like me.

00:36:31.463 --> 00:36:32.583
But...

00:36:33.583 --> 00:36:36.303
how am I supposed to stop myself, Win?

00:36:42.623 --> 00:36:43.903
So?

00:36:44.543 --> 00:36:45.903
Did you understand?

00:36:49.343 --> 00:36:50.783
Just now...

00:36:51.303 --> 00:36:53.103
what did you tell me?

00:36:53.503 --> 00:36:56.023
It felt really good.

00:36:59.303 --> 00:37:00.983
If it felt good...

00:37:02.263 --> 00:37:03.303
that’s good.

00:37:04.063 --> 00:37:05.783
Because what I was

00:37:05.783 --> 00:37:07.583
actually trying to tell you was...

00:37:17.543 --> 00:37:18.783
Focus on your training

00:37:18.823 --> 00:37:20.503
and stop being ridiculous.

00:37:28.183 --> 00:37:29.223
Alright.

00:37:29.223 --> 00:37:31.863
That’s it for today’s class.

00:38:15.023 --> 00:38:17.183
Win Pawee is really doing the film?

00:38:17.703 --> 00:38:19.103
Congratulations.

00:38:20.263 --> 00:38:21.823
I have a gift for you too.

00:38:22.943 --> 00:38:24.303
A cactus?

00:38:39.658 --> 00:38:41.538
Can we get a photo with this camera?

00:38:41.578 --> 00:38:43.058
This side too, please.

00:38:43.098 --> 00:38:45.818
- Over here as well.
- Perfect.

00:38:46.338 --> 00:38:47.338
Yes.

00:38:47.538 --> 00:38:48.698
I’m a little excited,

00:38:48.698 --> 00:38:50.858
but working with familiar faces

00:38:50.898 --> 00:38:52.778
makes me feel at ease.

00:38:52.818 --> 00:38:54.538
P’Waan is so beautiful.

00:38:55.378 --> 00:38:56.618
Take lots of photos.

00:38:56.658 --> 00:38:57.898
P’Waanwaan,

00:38:57.898 --> 00:39:00.698
who’s going to be the male lead opposite May?

00:39:00.738 --> 00:39:03.178
- Right?
- I’m dying to spill it.

00:39:03.178 --> 00:39:05.418
But the director wants it to be a surprise.

00:39:05.458 --> 00:39:07.258
So let’s wait

00:39:07.258 --> 00:39:08.738
for the director to reveal it.

00:39:08.778 --> 00:39:10.698
It’ll be more fun that way.

00:39:11.578 --> 00:39:12.618
But...

00:39:12.618 --> 00:39:14.658
Could it be Gam?

00:39:14.698 --> 00:39:17.778
Since P’Waanwaan is involved in the project?

00:39:17.818 --> 00:39:19.738
- Maybe.
- Also...

00:39:19.778 --> 00:39:21.378
There’s inside gossip

00:39:21.418 --> 00:39:22.618
that P’Waanwaan

00:39:22.658 --> 00:39:24.698
met with the director all week.

00:39:24.738 --> 00:39:25.978
Tell you what…

00:39:26.018 --> 00:39:27.938
let’s wait for the director’s surprise.

00:39:27.938 --> 00:39:30.378
We’ll all find out together.

00:39:30.618 --> 00:39:32.378
But for now, photos.

00:39:32.418 --> 00:39:34.338
Let’s get some big, clear shots.

00:39:34.378 --> 00:39:35.578
Once the crowd swarms in,

00:39:35.618 --> 00:39:39.378
- you won’t get big, clear shots.
- Got it.

00:39:39.418 --> 00:39:41.098
Big shots, please.

00:39:41.378 --> 00:39:42.498
How did he get here?

00:39:44.658 --> 00:39:45.658
Win.

00:39:45.698 --> 00:39:46.778
That must’ve been hard.

00:39:46.778 --> 00:39:48.098
How did you get here?

00:39:48.258 --> 00:39:50.578
- Win!
- You know him?

00:40:16.298 --> 00:40:17.378
May.

00:40:21.018 --> 00:40:22.818
I need to talk to you.

00:40:25.458 --> 00:40:27.698
Can I get Director Tong’s number?

00:40:27.738 --> 00:40:29.098
I want to speak with him.

00:40:29.818 --> 00:40:30.818
Sure.

00:40:30.858 --> 00:40:33.018
So you’re accepting the role?

00:40:34.898 --> 00:40:36.418
You’ll find out soon.

00:40:43.538 --> 00:40:44.898
Hello, P’Tong.

00:40:45.738 --> 00:40:48.698
Thank you so much for agreeing to do my film.

00:40:49.258 --> 00:40:50.698
My pleasure.

00:40:51.458 --> 00:40:52.618
But...

00:40:52.698 --> 00:40:55.098
don’t forget what we agreed on.

00:40:56.778 --> 00:40:58.538
Let’s finish here first,

00:40:58.538 --> 00:40:59.818
then we’ll talk.

00:41:01.258 --> 00:41:02.378
Alright.

00:41:08.298 --> 00:41:11.218
Can we get a little hug, please?

00:41:11.258 --> 00:41:12.298
Here.

00:41:12.298 --> 00:41:14.698
Win Pawee is really doing the film?

00:41:15.218 --> 00:41:16.298
What made you

00:41:16.338 --> 00:41:19.298
decide to return after three years?

00:41:22.378 --> 00:41:23.698
The reason is...

00:41:25.858 --> 00:41:26.898
someone.

00:41:26.898 --> 00:41:29.418
Someone.

00:41:29.458 --> 00:41:31.258
- Who?
- Who could it be?

00:41:38.458 --> 00:41:41.098
When you say “someone,”

00:41:41.138 --> 00:41:42.818
do you mean May?

00:41:43.978 --> 00:41:46.778
- Is it May?
- Is it her?

00:41:47.298 --> 00:41:49.098
I meant P’Tong.

00:41:52.058 --> 00:41:53.298
I worked with P’Tong

00:41:53.338 --> 00:41:55.058
when I first entered the industry.

00:41:55.098 --> 00:41:56.898
Then we went our separate ways.

00:41:57.098 --> 00:41:59.098
But I’ve always missed him.

00:41:59.818 --> 00:42:01.338
So sweet.

00:42:01.378 --> 00:42:03.458
He’s my benefactor.

00:42:03.498 --> 00:42:06.978
You could say he’s the one
who delivered me into this industry.

00:42:07.018 --> 00:42:08.938
That’s so sweet. She never forgot.

00:42:09.058 --> 00:42:10.258
And about the leaked photos…

00:42:10.298 --> 00:42:12.778
the news about you and May…

00:42:12.818 --> 00:42:14.498
was that a PR stunt?

00:42:15.218 --> 00:42:16.538
Was it?

00:42:17.658 --> 00:42:19.578
It wasn’t PR at all.

00:42:20.298 --> 00:42:22.138
It just happened by chance.

00:42:22.178 --> 00:42:24.338
May had an accident and hurt her leg.

00:42:24.338 --> 00:42:25.698
She couldn’t drive herself,

00:42:25.738 --> 00:42:27.978
so I offered to take her home.

00:42:28.818 --> 00:42:32.738
- I see.
- Then about the clip from three years ago…

00:42:32.778 --> 00:42:34.698
It was a long time ago, that’s true,

00:42:34.738 --> 00:42:36.818
but ever since it happened,

00:42:36.858 --> 00:42:38.378
you’ve never

00:42:38.418 --> 00:42:41.098
held a press conference to
explain what happened.

00:42:41.138 --> 00:42:42.898
- Or clarified anything.
- Right.

00:42:42.898 --> 00:42:45.378
Can you tell us what really happened?

00:42:45.378 --> 00:42:46.858
Just a little?

00:42:46.858 --> 00:42:48.538
- Could you clarify?
- Please clarify.

00:42:48.538 --> 00:42:50.818
- Anything you want to say?
- It was huge back then.

00:42:51.738 --> 00:42:52.978
Can you clarify?

00:42:53.498 --> 00:42:54.858
It was a long time ago.

00:42:54.858 --> 00:42:56.698
I’d rather not comment.

00:42:59.458 --> 00:43:01.818
How about we talk about the film instead?

00:43:02.698 --> 00:43:05.618
If you have questions, I’ll answer them all.

00:43:05.658 --> 00:43:08.298
- Really?
- Go ahead, ask. I’ll answer what I can.

00:43:09.018 --> 00:43:11.218
- Let’s go, Gam. Time to leave.
- Go ahead, ask. I’ll answer.

00:43:11.658 --> 00:43:12.818
Wait.

00:43:13.058 --> 00:43:14.298
Why?

00:43:14.338 --> 00:43:16.618
Shouldn’t we wait for interviews first?

00:43:17.378 --> 00:43:19.738
With a minor role like yours,

00:43:19.778 --> 00:43:21.218
who’d want to interview you?

00:43:21.218 --> 00:43:22.818
Oh, P’Waanwaan.

00:43:22.978 --> 00:43:25.378
Just getting to act with Win and May

00:43:25.378 --> 00:43:27.338
already makes me so happy.

00:43:27.378 --> 00:43:29.418
Please don’t be upset.

00:43:29.778 --> 00:43:30.778
Listen.

00:43:30.778 --> 00:43:31.818
My artist

00:43:31.818 --> 00:43:33.658
is never number three or four.

00:43:33.698 --> 00:43:35.538
Only number one.

00:43:35.578 --> 00:43:36.698
Remember that.

00:43:39.298 --> 00:43:40.978
- True fan.
- That pillow’s doomed.

00:43:54.938 --> 00:43:56.818
Congratulations.

00:43:58.578 --> 00:43:59.978
What are you doing?

00:44:02.978 --> 00:44:03.978
Hey.

00:44:06.058 --> 00:44:07.978
Are you celebrating New Year?

00:44:09.978 --> 00:44:11.338
You don’t like it?

00:44:11.378 --> 00:44:13.698
I set this up just for you.

00:44:17.578 --> 00:44:20.218
If this is your best effort,

00:44:20.538 --> 00:44:22.098
don’t bother next time.

00:44:23.418 --> 00:44:25.098
Remember that.

00:44:26.458 --> 00:44:28.218
I’m kidding.

00:44:28.218 --> 00:44:29.418
Thank you.

00:44:31.778 --> 00:44:33.818
I have a gift for you too.

00:44:49.378 --> 00:44:50.898
Is it cute?

00:44:55.298 --> 00:44:56.778
A cactus?

00:44:57.218 --> 00:44:59.258
It’s not just any cactus.

00:44:59.258 --> 00:45:00.738
The species is called

00:45:00.778 --> 00:45:02.298
Echinopsis calochlora.

00:45:03.018 --> 00:45:04.218
And

00:45:04.258 --> 00:45:06.018
I really love the name.

00:45:06.058 --> 00:45:08.658
They say when it blooms,

00:45:08.658 --> 00:45:10.418
the flowers are white,

00:45:10.458 --> 00:45:12.578
big and beautiful.

00:45:12.618 --> 00:45:14.538
I used to grow one as a kid,

00:45:14.578 --> 00:45:17.218
but I never saw it bloom.

00:45:17.258 --> 00:45:18.338
Maybe

00:45:18.338 --> 00:45:20.938
because I wasn’t up in the sky like you.

00:45:20.978 --> 00:45:22.258
Up in the sky?

00:45:22.258 --> 00:45:23.778
I’m not dead yet.

00:45:23.778 --> 00:45:25.818
That’s not what I meant.

00:45:25.858 --> 00:45:26.938
I mean,

00:45:26.938 --> 00:45:29.498
you’re a star. A superstar.

00:45:30.138 --> 00:45:32.418
You don’t like it?

00:45:35.258 --> 00:45:36.418
I do.

00:45:37.218 --> 00:45:39.538
Congratulations again, Win.

00:45:40.858 --> 00:45:43.098
Thank you again as well.

00:45:47.378 --> 00:45:49.178
Being up in the sky…

00:45:49.218 --> 00:45:51.898
it must feel really good, right?

00:45:54.418 --> 00:45:56.018
Maybe it’s not that great.

00:45:58.218 --> 00:45:59.498
Why not?

00:46:00.418 --> 00:46:03.578
We think stars are beautiful
because they’re far away.

00:46:05.858 --> 00:46:08.058
But up close,

00:46:08.898 --> 00:46:11.378
they’re just huge rocks…

00:46:11.978 --> 00:46:13.338
rough,

00:46:13.378 --> 00:46:15.458
covered in craters.

00:46:17.458 --> 00:46:18.458
But...

00:46:18.778 --> 00:46:21.298
even if we know

00:46:21.338 --> 00:46:23.058
that’s what they’re really like,

00:46:24.058 --> 00:46:25.138
we still don’t stop

00:46:25.178 --> 00:46:27.778
wanting to travel toward them, do we?

00:46:36.418 --> 00:46:37.618
Wanneung,

00:46:40.498 --> 00:46:41.898
someday,

00:46:42.018 --> 00:46:44.698
you’ll become the star you dream of.

00:46:45.778 --> 00:46:46.978
Trust me.

00:46:55.698 --> 00:46:57.778
The star is right here.

00:47:03.538 --> 00:47:05.178
Look, Win.

00:47:07.378 --> 00:47:08.978
It’s right here.

00:47:14.338 --> 00:47:16.378
Doesn’t look close at all.

00:47:17.098 --> 00:47:19.898
I mean I’m close to becoming a star.

00:47:29.418 --> 00:47:30.778
Over there.

00:47:30.818 --> 00:47:31.818
Where?

00:47:32.338 --> 00:47:34.458
- There, there.
- That one?

00:47:34.818 --> 00:47:36.098
A shooting star.

00:47:36.538 --> 00:47:37.898
Make a wish, quick.

00:47:38.018 --> 00:47:39.898
- I don’t see anything.
- There!

00:47:39.938 --> 00:47:42.178
- Where?
- Close your eyes and wish now.

00:47:47.418 --> 00:47:48.418
Hey.

00:47:48.858 --> 00:47:50.498
Don’t lie down and pray.

00:47:51.458 --> 00:47:53.698
That’s not how you make a wish.

00:48:55.698 --> 00:48:56.898
Wanneung.

00:48:58.658 --> 00:48:59.978
Wanneung.

00:49:04.738 --> 00:49:06.538
What is it, Win?

00:49:06.618 --> 00:49:07.818
The power’s out.

00:49:07.858 --> 00:49:10.098
Let me sleep here. I’m scared of ghosts.

00:49:13.498 --> 00:49:16.378
I can sense some strange energy around here.

00:49:20.138 --> 00:49:21.898
Since you moved in,

00:49:21.898 --> 00:49:23.858
how many times has the power gone out?

00:49:23.898 --> 00:49:26.618
You have your own bed.
Why not sleep there?

00:49:26.658 --> 00:49:28.778
Do you know how cramped this is?

00:49:28.938 --> 00:49:32.538
Just let me sleep here.

00:50:21.858 --> 00:50:23.498
I can do it, Director.

00:51:25.978 --> 00:51:27.778
I’ll put my name on the line.

00:51:27.778 --> 00:51:29.098
She can do it.

00:51:29.098 --> 00:51:30.698
And she’s perfect for this role.

00:51:30.778 --> 00:51:32.578
Did you sign a contract with P’Waanwaan?

00:51:32.578 --> 00:51:34.938
Yes. You’re happy for me, right?

00:52:02.863 --> 00:52:04.183
Hello?

00:52:05.303 --> 00:52:06.543
What?

00:52:08.783 --> 00:52:11.263
One moment, please.

00:52:17.463 --> 00:52:18.863
Yes, Waanwaan’s mom.

00:52:20.623 --> 00:52:21.943
What?

00:52:26.783 --> 00:52:27.983
Alright.

00:52:28.263 --> 00:52:30.143
See you, P’Waanwaan.

00:53:24.383 --> 00:53:25.663
Win.

00:53:25.663 --> 00:53:26.863
Wanneung.

00:53:27.743 --> 00:53:29.063
Where are you going?

00:53:31.223 --> 00:53:32.863
I’m heading to work.

00:53:32.903 --> 00:53:34.383
What about you?

00:53:38.743 --> 00:53:40.143
Going to see Tom.

00:53:40.503 --> 00:53:42.503
So you’re off to work now?

00:53:42.543 --> 00:53:43.983
Want me to drop you off?

00:53:44.423 --> 00:53:45.703
No, no, it’s fine.

00:53:45.703 --> 00:53:47.503
The production van’s picking me up.

00:53:47.543 --> 00:53:49.663
I’ve got to go. I’ll be late. Bye.

00:54:02.503 --> 00:54:03.903
I’m really glad

00:54:03.943 --> 00:54:06.063
I didn’t ditch you at the press conference.

00:54:07.383 --> 00:54:08.983
I wouldn’t ditch you.

00:54:09.503 --> 00:54:11.743
But you can’t ditch me either.

00:54:15.263 --> 00:54:16.263
Well...

00:54:16.663 --> 00:54:17.743
about that...

00:54:18.703 --> 00:54:19.823
I was planning to…

00:54:19.823 --> 00:54:22.063
- to…
- Is there a problem?

00:54:26.143 --> 00:54:27.183
Well...

00:54:27.343 --> 00:54:29.983
If you can’t do what I asked,

00:54:31.983 --> 00:54:33.663
I’ll have to withdraw.

00:54:39.143 --> 00:54:40.263
Win...

00:54:41.103 --> 00:54:43.583
It’s an international co-production.

00:54:44.303 --> 00:54:46.983
I need to discuss it with the investors first.

00:54:47.303 --> 00:54:49.063
And it’s not like...

00:54:49.223 --> 00:54:51.263
you can just cast anyone you want.

00:54:51.423 --> 00:54:53.743
It’s not that easy to squeeze someone in.

00:54:54.063 --> 00:54:55.103
Most importantly,

00:54:55.143 --> 00:54:57.263
the character has to fit the role.

00:54:57.303 --> 00:54:58.383
It has to match.

00:54:59.943 --> 00:55:00.983
But...

00:55:02.623 --> 00:55:04.703
(Wanneung)

00:55:10.383 --> 00:55:12.663
I’ll put my name on the line.

00:55:12.703 --> 00:55:14.303
She can do it.

00:55:14.543 --> 00:55:16.383
And she’s perfect for this role.

00:55:16.903 --> 00:55:18.583
Just give her a chance.

00:55:51.503 --> 00:55:53.583
Who were you calling, Wanneung?

00:55:55.303 --> 00:55:56.703
A friend.

00:55:56.743 --> 00:55:59.783
Why? Don’t you trust me anymore?

00:56:02.183 --> 00:56:03.463
Well...

00:56:03.503 --> 00:56:05.143
If you’re not comfortable, then...

00:56:05.183 --> 00:56:06.663
you don’t have to sign.

00:56:07.703 --> 00:56:09.103
I’ll sign.

00:56:12.343 --> 00:56:14.223
The last page, dear.

00:56:15.223 --> 00:56:16.263
Okay.

00:56:20.823 --> 00:56:23.863
(Wanneung Rojanapanphang)

00:56:29.503 --> 00:56:30.983
One more copy, sweetheart.

00:56:31.023 --> 00:56:32.063
Okay.

00:56:37.943 --> 00:56:39.983
Let me check the details first.

00:56:43.663 --> 00:56:45.103
All done.

00:56:45.143 --> 00:56:47.063
You’re officially an actress now, Wanneung.

00:56:47.103 --> 00:56:48.583
Congratulations.

00:56:48.583 --> 00:56:52.263
Welcome to the entertainment industry.

00:56:53.463 --> 00:56:56.263
From now on, you can tell everyone

00:56:56.303 --> 00:56:57.863
you’re under my management.

00:56:57.863 --> 00:57:00.663
Before this, I didn’t want you to tell anyone…

00:57:00.663 --> 00:57:01.943
you understand, right?

00:57:01.943 --> 00:57:04.663
People like to use my name without permission.

00:57:05.223 --> 00:57:07.223
So I wanted to keep it a secret

00:57:07.263 --> 00:57:09.183
until we signed the contract.

00:57:09.463 --> 00:57:11.223
I understand, P’Waanwaan.

00:57:11.263 --> 00:57:13.543
Thank you so much.

00:57:13.943 --> 00:57:16.143
Stick with me and you’ll get good jobs.

00:57:16.183 --> 00:57:17.463
Don’t worry.

00:57:18.143 --> 00:57:19.383
I can’t believe it.

00:57:19.423 --> 00:57:21.743
I actually signed with you.

00:57:21.743 --> 00:57:24.663
Why does everything feel so fast?

00:57:24.903 --> 00:57:27.703
If I find a talented kid like you
and don’t grab you fast,

00:57:27.743 --> 00:57:29.703
what if someone else snatches you?

00:57:30.303 --> 00:57:33.103
If you say that, I’ll start floating.

00:57:33.103 --> 00:57:35.183
I’m not dreaming, right?

00:57:35.383 --> 00:57:36.823
Dreaming?

00:57:36.863 --> 00:57:38.863
- Hey.
- P’Waanwaan!

00:57:38.863 --> 00:57:40.063
Does that hurt?

00:57:40.103 --> 00:57:42.463
- It hurts.
- Then you’re not dreaming.

00:57:45.943 --> 00:57:47.623
If anything comes up,

00:57:47.663 --> 00:57:49.303
I’ll contact you right away.

00:57:49.623 --> 00:57:50.903
Okay.

00:57:51.303 --> 00:57:53.303
Here’s one for you. Keep it.

00:57:53.623 --> 00:57:54.863
Okay.

00:57:55.463 --> 00:57:57.263
Keep it safe. Don’t lose it.

00:59:30.903 --> 00:59:32.983
Win.

00:59:36.023 --> 00:59:38.383
Win, I have good news to tell you.

00:59:38.423 --> 00:59:40.663
- I…
- Wait, don’t say anything yet.

00:59:47.423 --> 00:59:49.863
Don’t you notice anything?

01:00:08.303 --> 01:00:10.063
Did you redecorate?

01:00:10.623 --> 01:00:11.743
Right?

01:00:12.703 --> 01:00:15.903
But everything still looks the same.

01:00:19.063 --> 01:00:20.663
This is the same.

01:00:21.103 --> 01:00:22.503
The blanket’s the same.

01:00:24.663 --> 01:00:25.783
Win?

01:00:26.183 --> 01:00:27.183
Win?

01:00:27.783 --> 01:00:29.383
Where are you going?

01:00:32.383 --> 01:00:35.103
Win!

01:00:35.103 --> 01:00:37.783
Can you come out and talk to me?

01:00:38.063 --> 01:00:39.783
I have good news.

01:00:39.823 --> 01:00:41.543
Come hear it, please.

01:00:41.583 --> 01:00:43.183
Please, Win.

01:01:09.423 --> 01:01:10.463
Wanneung.

01:01:11.703 --> 01:01:13.663
Did you sign a contract with P’Waanwaan?

01:01:13.863 --> 01:01:16.223
Yes. You’re happy for me, right?

01:01:16.263 --> 01:01:20.063
I signed with the number one talent manager.

01:01:21.583 --> 01:01:23.063
Look into my eyes.

01:01:23.303 --> 01:01:24.903
See if I’m happy.

01:01:24.903 --> 01:01:26.543
And what I want to tell you.

01:01:32.863 --> 01:01:34.063
You want to say...

01:01:34.103 --> 01:01:36.383
you’re happy I’m about to succeed,

01:01:36.423 --> 01:01:39.343
and you’ll stay by my side forever.

01:01:39.383 --> 01:01:42.903
And you also want to tell me...

01:01:43.623 --> 01:01:46.583
that you like me, right, Win?

01:02:23.223 --> 01:02:24.383
Go pack your bags.

01:02:24.423 --> 01:02:26.783
Where are you sending me?

01:02:29.223 --> 01:02:30.783
So pretty.

01:02:30.823 --> 01:02:32.903
From now on, if you’re going to be an actress,

01:02:32.943 --> 01:02:34.863
you need focus in your acting, okay?

01:02:34.903 --> 01:02:36.383
You and that woman…

01:02:36.423 --> 01:02:38.343
there’s nothing special between you, right?

01:02:38.383 --> 01:02:40.943
Tom knows I’m scarred from love,

01:02:40.983 --> 01:02:42.503
so I don’t dare open my heart to anyone.

01:02:42.543 --> 01:02:43.663
But maybe

01:02:43.663 --> 01:02:46.583
she’s the one who’ll make
you brave enough to try again.

01:02:46.823 --> 01:02:48.983
Can I ask you something, Wanneung?

01:02:49.023 --> 01:02:50.263
Of course.

01:02:54.263 --> 01:02:56.023
- Ouch. Wait a second.

01:02:56.263 --> 01:02:57.583
- I can’t lift you.

01:02:58.863 --> 01:03:00.343
I almost fell just now.

01:03:00.383 --> 01:03:03.463
- Sorry.
- I’m losing weight, okay?

01:03:03.743 --> 01:03:05.783
I didn’t mean to go that hard.

01:03:09.143 --> 01:03:11.103
- One more time, sweetheart.
- It won’t come out.

01:03:11.103 --> 01:03:13.783
- Is it turning?
- It is, but it won’t come off.

01:03:14.823 --> 01:03:15.943
Hold on.

01:03:16.783 --> 01:03:18.263
(There, there. Good job.)

01:03:20.223 --> 01:03:23.743
Belle almost burst a tire just now.
(Making up.)